value.title: Fact check: Trump falsely claims 'illegal ballots' are changing the election
value.excerpt: In a tweet thread Saturday morning President Donald Trump threw out baseless claims suggesting that "tens of thousands" of illegal ballots are being used to change the results in key states.

value.title: Schumer sings 'God Bless America' after Biden projected winner
value.excerpt: Sen. Chuck Schumer celebrated President Trump's projected defeat by singing a rendition of "God Bless America," and telling the former Manhattan resident it's time to pack up and go home to his new home state of Florida.

value.title: Flashback: Trump in October said, 'Could you imagine if I lose?'
value.excerpt: President Trump mocked the idea of losing to former Vice President Joe Biden during a campaign rally less than a month before Election Day, pointing to rival Joe Biden as the "worst candidate in the history of presidential politics."

value.title: Pence continues Hoosier streak of one-term Republican vice presidents
value.excerpt: With Vice President Mike Pence projected to lose his reelection bid, none of the four Republican vice presidents hailing from Indiana ever have served more than one term.

value.title: PHOTOS: After Biden declared president, crowds take to streets in NYC, Washington, DC
Rudy Giuliani releases politics video pausing for a sponsored cigar commercial and blaming Fox News for Trump's defeat
value.excerpt: In the YouTube series, entitled 'Rudy Giuliani's Common Sense,' Donald Trump's personal attorney discusses political issues and current affairs weekly.

value.title: Senate GOP declare "Senate is last line of defense" after Biden-Harris projected win
value.excerpt: With President-elect Joe Biden's projected electoral college victory, the nation's attention will now turn to the races which could determine the partisan balance of the Senate — and so determine whether Biden's agenda is implemented in his first term in office.

value.title: Breakingviews - Biden win sets scene for storm before the calm
value.excerpt: Americans chose Joe Biden as their 46th president. That should usher in a more predictable period for policymaking, and decisive action on containing Covid-19. But he faces three major challenges: voters’ effective rejection of his party’s punchier ideas,

value.title: Biden says he's 'honored and humbled' and calls for unity after major networks declare him the 46th president
value.excerpt: President-elect Biden said in a statement it was time for "America to heal." Vice President-elect Harris said, "we have a lot of work ahead of us."

value.title: Election 2020 exit polls: Political pundits utterly failed to predict Donald Trump's voters
value.excerpt: How could the polling be so wrong that it seems Donald Trump gained support among women and racial minorities? There really was a shy Trump voter.

value.title: Trump's attacks on mail-in ballots rankle some military vets
value.excerpt: Now, with his presidency on the line, he’s casting suspicion on a tool of participatory democracy — the mail-in ballot — that has allowed U.S. military personnel to vote while serving far from home since the War of 1812.

value.title: Democrat in Greenwich 'ecstatic' Kamala Harris on cusp of being VP
value.excerpt: Joe Biden seemed poised on Friday to take Pennsylvania and, most likely, the presidency. The victory, if and when it comes, was applauded by local experts.

value.title: Biden claims 'mandate' while election vs. Trump remains undecided
value.excerpt: Joe Biden didn't declare victory Friday night over President Trump in the race for the White House, but he emphasized that he's "going to win" the presidential election.

value.title: Bolsonaro abandons 'friend' Trump after 2020 election, says he's 'not the most important person in the world'
value.excerpt: Tthe Brazilian president has often been called the "Trump of the Tropics," and even echoed the US president's attacks on "fake news" media.

value.title: Bernie Sanders thanks, praises progressives for 'Biden's victory' before race is called
value.excerpt: Sen. Bernie Sanders thanked progressives Friday afternoon for aiding Democratic nominee Joe Biden’s 2020 presidential efforts – even with the race still too close to call.

value.title: Where is Mike Pence?
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence hasn’t been seen publicly for three days. Pence, who heads the coronavirus task force and serves as president of the Senate, was not with the president in the briefing room Thursday night.

value.title: Home vandalized after California man hangs effigy of Biden
value.excerpt: The Northern California home of a supporter of President Donald Trump was vandalized Friday after an effigy of Joe Biden accompanied by the word "cheater" was hung from its second-story roof with a rope,

value.title: Biden on verge of winning U.S. presidency, leads in Pennsylvania, Georgia
value.excerpt: Democrat Joe Biden stood on the verge of winning the U.S. presidency on Friday, as he expanded his narrow leads over President Donald Trump in the battleground states of Pennsylvania and Georgia three days after polls closed.

value.title: Kamala Harris in Detroit on Election Day to rally support: 'Have faith in the American people'
value.excerpt: Harris encouraged voters to trust their neighbors and the electoral process before canvassing throughout metro Detroit.

value.title: Minnesota 'Squad' member says Trump attack on her during campaign was a mistake
value.excerpt: Rep. Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., on Thursday said Trump "effed around" in deciding to attack her as a way to win over Minnesota voters.

value.title: Trump campaign hasn't provided evidence to back up claim of Wisconsin election 'irregularities'
value.excerpt: Trump and officials with his campaign have floated vague accusations with no evidence of election tampering in Wisconsin.

value.title: Trump Names Danly to Head FERC, Replacing Chatterjee
value.excerpt: Neil Chatterjee, who has backed policies in support of clean energy, is being replaced as head of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission by fellow commissioner James Danly.

value.title: Trump 'likely' to run again in 2024 if he loses: Mick Mulvaney
value.excerpt: Trump's former acting White House chief of staff Mick Mulvaney says the president isn't ready to bow out of politics.

value.title: If Trump loses, he will regret 'denigrating mail-in voting': York
value.excerpt: If President Trump loses the election to Joe Biden as current vote tallies indicate, he could regret warning against mail-in voting, Fox News contributor Byron York argued Friday.

value.title: Trump Jr. calls out '2024 GOP hopefuls' for 'total lack of action' in ballot-counting fight
value.excerpt: Donald Trump Jr. pressured potential 2024 GOP contenders to vocally support President Trump as the president continues to air often unfounded grievances about alleged voter fraud.
